00:00:03.340 --> 00:00:09.420
It's an annual ethnic knives and handicrafts Fair in Yakutsk.

00:00:10.680 --> 00:00:14.820
Local craftsmen show their best artwork.

00:00:15.000 --> 00:00:19.820
And you can feel the soul of northern people and its traditions.

00:00:33.480 --> 00:00:36.320
Yakut knife looks simple.

00:00:36.320 --> 00:00:42.920
It has nothing superfluous. Everything is subject to functionality.

00:00:43.700 --> 00:00:51.560
Generations of fishermen and hunters, residents of taiga and tundra made Yakut knife a perfect.

00:00:51.560 --> 00:00:58.060
Over the centuries, people have found a knife shape that best convenient in the conditions of the North.

00:00:58.060 --> 00:01:01.960
The knife handle made from birch burl.

00:01:01.960 --> 00:01:05.520
Handle is thick and egg-shaped in cross-section.

00:01:05.520 --> 00:01:10.720
It fits the hand, and it does not slip and does not freeze in the cold.

00:01:11.160 --> 00:01:16.720
Blade is asymmetric with fuller.

00:01:16.720 --> 00:01:25.420
Yakut knife is very convenient to process a wood, to carve a meat and to slice frozen fish.

00:01:25.420 --> 00:01:29.220
It's very convenient to use it when wearing mittens.

00:01:29.220 --> 00:01:33.960
Knife traditionally has wedge blade profile. So it is easy to sharpening.

00:01:33.960 --> 00:01:37.340
Now this craftsman will show his knife.

00:01:37.340 --> 00:01:42.320
He easily pierced a coin.

00:01:47.080 --> 00:01:51.440
And the knife is still sharp as a razor.

00:01:52.200 --> 00:01:55.160
The scabbard is also unusual.

00:01:55.160 --> 00:02:01.280
It's traditionally made of two wooden inserts sheathed by a skin.

00:02:01.280 --> 00:02:07.460
Only third of the handle protrudes from the scabbard, and knife held firmly.

00:02:07.460 --> 00:02:12.160
Scabbard is freely attached to the waist-belt by soft strap.

00:02:12.620 --> 00:02:22.500
This is Batiya - Yakut Naginata - ancient martial and hunting cold weapon.

00:02:57.140 --> 00:03:03.340
Bone carvers turn a usual knife into an artwork.

00:03:06.403 --> 00:03:13.343
To make such masterpieces they used mammoth bone and precious metals.

00:03:17.540 --> 00:03:23.420
Author spent two years to make this miniature.

00:03:42.100 --> 00:03:51.640
The Fair has always attracted the attention of many people interested in not only knives, but also other items of ethnic handicrafts.

